e:T544,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How long does sewer line replacement take in Nashville?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most residential sewer lateral replacements in Nashville take 1–2 days, including excavation, replacement, backfill, and Metro inspection. Trenchless replacements often finish in a single day. Larger or more complex jobs (city right-of-way coordination, multi-method approaches) can run 2–4 days."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Will my insurance cover sewer line replacement?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Standard homeowner policies in Tennessee usually don't cover sewer lateral replacement (it's wear-and-tear, not sudden damage), but service-line add-on policies and some umbrella coverages do. We'll provide you with the photos, camera footage, and documentation you need to file a claim. We don't do the claim filing — that's between you and your carrier — but we make it easy on you."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you handle the permit and inspection for sewer and water line work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. We pull the Metro Nashville plumbing permit, coordinate the Metro inspection, and don't ask for final payment until the work is signed off. The permit cost is included in our flat quote."}}]}6:[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Services\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Sewer & Water Line Replacement\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services/sewer-water-line-replacement\"}]}"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$e"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Service\",\"name\":\"Sewer & Water Line Replacement\",\"description\":\"Sewer line and water service line replacement in Nashville. Trenchless and traditional methods. Pipe replacement and repair for residential and commercial properties. Permitted, bonded, insured.\",\"serviceType\":\"Sewer & Water Line Replacement\",\"url\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services/sewer-water-line-replacement\",\"provider\":{\"@id\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com#business\"},\"areaServed\":[{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"East Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Downtown Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Green Hills\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Belle Meade & West Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Brentwood\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Franklin\"}]}"}}],["$","article",null,{"children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-ink/10","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-7","children":[["$","nav",null,{"aria-label":"Breadcrumb","className":"text-sm text-ink-muted mb-6","children":["$","ol",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-forest","children":"Home"}]}],["$","li",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"/"}],["$","li",null,{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/services","className":"hover:text-forest","children":"Services"}]}],["$","li",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"/"}],["$","li",null,{"className":"text-ink","children":"Sewer & Water Lines"}]]}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"eyebrow mb-4","children":"Service"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl leading-[1.05] text-ink mb-6","children":["Sewer & Water Line Replacement"," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"italic text-forest","children":"in Nashville"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"font-display italic text-2xl text-ink-soft mb-7","children":"Underground pipe done right. No surprises."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"When the sewer or water line under your Nashville property fails, the work needs to be done by people who know Metro Nashville Codes, Metro Water Services connection requirements, and how to navigate the permit and inspection process without delays. We replace sewer laterals and water service lines across Davidson and Williamson counties — both trenchless (where appropriate) and traditional open-trench methods."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-5","children":["$","$Lf",null,{"defaultService":"sewer-water-line-replacement"}]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 lg:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-editorial","children":[["$","div","Sewer line replacement: trenchless vs. open trench",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Sewer line replacement: trenchless vs. open trench"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Trenchless sewer replacement (pipe bursting or pipe lining) is the right call when the existing line follows a relatively straight path, doesn't have significant collapses or back-pitched sections, and runs under landscaping, driveways, or hardscape you want to preserve. We use pipe bursting for full replacement (pulls a new HDPE line through the path of the old one), and CIPP lining for spot repairs where the host pipe is structurally sound but has cracks or small offsets. Traditional open-trench replacement is sometimes still the right answer — when the line has multiple major defects, has been re-routed multiple times, or runs in a path that would damage trenchless equipment. We'll tell you which method makes sense after a camera inspection."}]]}],["$","div","Water service line replacement",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Water service line replacement"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Nashville water service lines (the line from your meter to your house) most commonly fail in homes built before 1960, where the original copper, galvanized, or in some cases lead service lines have corroded or split. Symptoms: chronically low water pressure, discolored water at fixtures throughout the house, or a water bill that suddenly doubled from an underground leak. We replace water service lines with 1\" or 1.25\" Type K soft copper or PEX-A (depending on local code preference and run distance). Permits, Metro Water coordination, and pressure testing are included."}]]}],["$","div","Permits and what \"licensed, bonded, insured\" actually means in Nashville",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Permits and what \"licensed, bonded, insured\" actually means in Nashville"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Anyone touching the sewer lateral or water service line in Davidson County needs a Tennessee Master Plumber license, a Metro Nashville plumbing permit, and active bonding and insurance. Frank Sullivan is the licensed master plumber on record for every Joe B. Sullivan & Sons job — that means our permits get pulled correctly, our work passes inspection, and you're protected if something goes wrong. We file the permit, schedule the Metro inspection, and don't ask you for final payment until the inspection is signed off."}]]}],["$","div","What it costs",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"What it costs"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Sewer lateral replacement in the Nashville metro: $4,500–$12,000 depending on length, method (trenchless vs. open trench), depth, and whether the work crosses concrete, landscaping, or city right-of-way. Water service line replacement: $2,800–$7,500 depending on length, depth, and meter location. We provide flat-price quotes after a site visit and camera inspection — no estimates that balloon mid-job. Most sewer and water line projects are completed in 1–3 days."}]]}]]}]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"bg-bone-100/60 border-y border-ink/10 py-16 lg:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"eyebrow mb-3","children":"Common questions"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-display text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-ink mb-10 leading-tight","children":["Frequently asked about ","sewer & water lines"," in Nashville."]}],["$","dl",null,{"className":"space-y-6","children":[["$","div","How long does sewer line replacement take in Nashville?",{"className":"card-press p-6","children":[["$","dt",null,{"className":"font-display text-xl text-ink mb-3","children":"How long does sewer line replacement take in Nashville?"}],["$","dd",null,{"className":"text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Most residential sewer lateral replacements in Nashville take 1–2 days, including excavation, replacement, backfill, and Metro inspection. Trenchless replacements often finish in a single day. Larger or more complex jobs (city right-of-way coordination, multi-method approaches) can run 2–4 days."}]]}],["$","div","Will my insurance cover sewer line replacement?",{"className":"card-press p-6","children":[["$","dt",null,{"className":"font-display text-xl text-ink mb-3","children":"Will my insurance cover sewer line replacement?"}],["$","dd",null,{"className":"text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Standard homeowner policies in Tennessee usually don't cover sewer lateral replacement (it's wear-and-tear, not sudden damage), but service-line add-on policies and some umbrella coverages do. We'll provide you with the photos, camera footage, and documentation you need to file a claim. We don't do the claim filing — that's between you and your carrier — but we make it easy on you."}]]}],["$","div","Do you handle the permit and inspection for sewer and water line work?",{"className":"card-press p-6","chil